<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A9406008003">
<title>
Washer Linked Wiper Circuit
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Make sure that windshield wiper switch is at “OFF” position.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect battery positive (+) terminal to terminal “8” and its negative (–) terminal to terminal “5”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect voltmeter positive lead to terminal “7” and its negative lead to terminal “5”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
When windshield washer switch is ON, check that voltage changes as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If check result is not as specified, replace wiper and washer switch.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A940022.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "90.868mm" ver = "01" gw = "202" gh = "241"/>
